x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
.The resulting cross sections are compared to
previously published data and the S-32(d,P(0))S-33 and
S-32(d,P(1))S-33 cross sections are also compared
directly to the rutherford cross section.
The hvec an2500 van de graaff accelerator.
Two different experimentals methods were used
one  using a thin Cd-S film and the other using a thick
Zn-S target.
The errors is the standard deviation in the counting
statistics of the appropriate sulphur reaction.
From HTTP://IBASERVER.PHYSICS.ISU.EDU/SIGMABASE
- By compiler - the data, which are presented in data
section, are result of interpolation of experimental
data.
- By  authors - the thick film method was employed
at different incident beam energies and the results
were combined into a single cross section.
The  values  agree with our thin film results, which
generally exceed those of Saad et al (1966) by a factor
of 2. See REL -REF.
- By authors - the resulting cross sections were
normalized by directly comparing the yield of the
32-S(d,P0)33-S reaction to the elastic scatter yield.
- By compiler - all excitation energies were taken from
Table of Isotopes.
